{{Quote|I serve [[Khonshu]]. I'm his Avatar. Which means you are, too. Sort of. We protect the vulnerable and deliver Khonshu's justice to those who hurt them.|Marc Spector to Steven Grant|Summon the Suit}}
'''Marc Spector''' is a former [[United States Marine Corps|United States Marine]] and mercenary with {{WPS|dissociative identity disorder}}. During his childhood, Spector's brother [[Randall Spector|Randall]] drowned in a cave while they were playing, starting a strenuous and spiteful relationship with his [[Wendy Spector|mother]], who frequently abused him. To find comfort within himself, Spector's psyche formed an alter known as '''Steven Grant''', who had no memory of Spector's trauma. While he was on a mission in [[Egypt]], Spector was shot by his partner [[Raul Bushman]], but he was saved by [[Khonshu]], who transformed him into his Avatar and the vigilante '''Moon Knight'''. Soon after, he fell in love with and married [[Layla El-Faouly]]. Following his mother's death, the Grant alter resurfaced and relocated to [[London]] to become a [[National Art Gallery|museum]] worker, with Spector occasionally taking over the body to operate as Moon Knight.

Grant found himself in the middle of a [[Conspiracy to Release Ammit|conspiracy]] where a [[Disciples of Ammit|cult]] led by [[Arthur Harrow]] intended to release [[Ammit]], so he teamed up with his wife and Spector to stop him. Whenever Grant summoned his [[Moon Knight's Suit|suit]], he took the form of '''Mr. Knight'''. During their search for Ammit's tomb, Grant had complications with Spector, with the latter wanting to disappear after they defeated Harrow. Arriving at the tomb, Spector was shot and killed by Harrow before being transported to the [[Duat]]. As Grant discovered Spector's traumatic past, he fell into the Duat, resulting in Spector being able to pass on to the [[Field of Reeds]]. Spector was able to rescue Grant by sharing his balanced heart with him, and returned to life through the [[Gates of Osiris]]. Reuniting with Khonshu, Moon Knight and Mr. Knight, along with El-Faouly and help from their mysterious third alter, managed to [[Battle of Giza|defeat]] Harrow and prevent Ammit from enacting her judgment [[Earth|worldwide]]. In exchange for defeating Ammit, Spector and Grant were freed from Khonshu's servitude. However, their third alter, '''Jake Lockley''', began fronting and continued to serve Khonshu as his Avatar, [[Assassination of Arthur Harrow|executing]] both Harrow and Ammit.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
====Childhood in Chicago====
{{Quote|Keep an eye on your [[Randall Spector|brother]]. Okay?"<br>"Laters, gators.|[[Wendy Spector]] and Marc Spector|Asylum}}
Marc Spector was born into a Jewish household, to [[Wendy Spector|Wendy]] and [[Elias Spector]] on [[1987|March 9, 1987]] in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].<ref name="Passport"/> He later had a younger brother named [[Randall Spector|Randall]]. As a way to say goodbye to his mother, Spector often said "Laters, gators". Growing up, Spector and Randall maintained an amicable relationship, and would frequently masquerade and enact scenes from the adventure film ''[[Tomb Buster]]'', with Spector usually playing the role of the film's protagonist, the explorer Dr. [[Steven Grant (Fiction)|Steven Grant]].{{Ref|MK105}}

====Death of Randall Spector====
{{Quote|You were supposed to keep [[Randall Spector|him]] safe! You let him drown. This is all your fault!|[[Wendy Spector]] to Marc Spector|Asylum}}
[[File:Spector Family.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector spends quality time with his family]]
In [[1996]], during a family barbecue, Spector mocked [[Randall Spector]]'s drawing of a [[Fish|goldfish]] for having only one fin. While [[Elias Spector]] was building a [[Spector Residence|shed]], Spector urged his brother to explore a nearby cave before dinner, which they frequently visited in order to reenact more scenes of ''[[Tomb Buster]]''. They received permission from their mother [[Wendy Spector]], who reminded him to look after his brother before saying his signature goodbye.
[[File:Marc and Randall Spector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector and his [[Randall Spector|brother]] go explore further]]
Walking to the cave, they continued to act in character as [[Steven Grant (Fiction)|Steven Grant]] and [[Rosser]] from ''Tomb Buster''. Before entering the cave, it started to rain; Randall expressed hesitation to go into the cave due to their mother warning them not to go when it was raining, but Spector ignored him. Unfortunately, as they entered the cave, the rain only intensified, and further escalated into a heavy downpour. The cave began rapidly flooding with rainwater, trapping the children. While Spector was able to escape, Randall helplessly drowned, with Spector unable to save him.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Abused by his Mother====
[[File:Young Marc.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is furiously berated by his [[Wendy Spector|mother]]]]
{{Quote|We will fix this."<br>"You're supposed to fix this. I mean... Why haven't you?|[[Elias Spector]] and Marc Spector|Asylum}}
During [[Randall Spector]]'s shiva, Spector went downstairs to join the other mourners, but when the grieving [[Wendy Spector]] saw him, she immediately blamed him for his brother's death. As she furiously yelled at him in front of their other family, the upset Spector ran back upstairs. This began a strained relationship between Spector and his mother, as she initially grew reclusive from Spector, blaming him for Randall's death, and later deluding herself into thinking Spector planned it out, which caused Wendy to become abusive over time.
[[File:Marc & Elias.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector with his [[Elias Spector|father]] on his 10th birthday]]
On Spector's tenth birthday in [[1997|March 1997]], [[Elias Spector]] gave him a cake and sat down with him. Spector asked if his mother was coming, but his father told him that she was not well, but promised she would get better, making an excuse to justify her refusal to celebrate. Spector blew out the candles on his cake, missing one, and simply sat in sadness as his father blew out the remaining candle. As the years went by, the relationship between Marc and his mother escalated to domestic abuse, both verbal and physical, which was only made worse when she resorted to substance abuse.
[[File:Marc and Wendy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is harassed again by [[Wendy Spector]]]]
On Spector's twelfth birthday in [[1999|March 1999]], a drunken Wendy sat next to Spector, claiming that he had always hated his brother and that she should have known that he would kill him. Spector then left the table and ran up to his room, upset. He locked his bedroom door to keep his mother out, but she followed him and started banging on the door, demanding that he open it in a drunken fit.
[[File:Marc Spector develops DID.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector allows Grant to front]]
Fearful of his mother, Spector was crouched into a corner, where he began telling himself that Wendy was not his mother. Wanting to find comfort, the trauma of his mother's abuse resulted in Spector developing {{WPS|dissociative identity disorder}}, creating the alter, of a polite [[England|British]] boy named "Steven Grant", after the [[Steven Grant (Fiction)|character]] from ''[[Tomb Buster]]'', who was unaware of his brother's existence. After fronting, Grant told himself that the room was a mess and that he should clean it up for his mother. Eventually, Wendy pushed open the door, telling "Spector" that he should be punished, grabbing a nearby belt to whip him. Spector then began fronting again, so that Grant would not be the one that was punished and would have a chance to live a normal life, taking the physical abuse from his mother. Since Spector fronted to shield Grant from his mother's abuse, this convinced Grant that their mother was kind and loving, contrary to the reality that she was abusive and hated him.{{Ref|MK105}}
[[File:Elias Spector & Marc Spector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector decides to leave his [[Elias Spector|father]] alone]]
Over time, Spector's rage and aggression manifested into a third alter named Jake Lockley, who had a ruthless demeanor and spoke Spanish as his default language. However, neither Spector nor Grant were aware of Lockley's existence.{{Ref|MK106}} As Spector grew into a teenager, he immediately took the chance and left [[Spector Residence|home]]. On the neighborhood street outside their home, his [[Elias Spector|father]] begged him to stay, saying that his [[Wendy Spector|mother]] would get help, and that he could not lose another son. Spector expressed his anger at his mother, stating that Elias should have helped her years ago, and explained that was why he had to leave.{{Ref|MK105}}

===Becoming Moon Knight===
====Making a Deal with Khonshu====
[[File:Marc Spector injured.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector prepares himself for his own death]]
{{Quote|Do you swear to protect the travelers of the night and bring my vengeance to those who would do them harm?"<br>"Yes.|[[Khonshu]] and Marc Spector|Asylum}}
Upon leaving his abusive family home, Spector had no need for the others to front and thus was able to keep front under his control. Spector went on to join the [[United States Marine Corps]]. However, Spector entered a fugue state that caused him to go AWOL, leading to him being discharged. With limited options, Spector decided to become a mercenary, working under his former commanding officer, [[Raul Bushman]].{{Ref|MK105}}
[[File:Marc Spector becomes Khonshu's Avatar.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector makes a deal with [[Khonshu]]]]
In [[2018]], Spector survived the [[Snap]] and, in December of that year, was issued a new passport.<ref name="Passport"/> In [[2022]],{{Ref|MSTMCUAOT}} Spector worked alongside Bushman and [[Abdallah El-Faouly]] on a mission at a dig site in [[Egypt]]; however, Bushman became greedy and executed all the archaeologists with them. Spector unsuccessfully attempted to save them, but was shot by Bushman.{{Ref|MK104}} Having been left for dead by Bushman, Spector dragged himself to a nearby [[Khonshu's Temple|temple]], laying at the foot of a statue. Wishing the pain to end, Spector prepared to shoot himself. However, he was stopped by [[Khonshu]], the Egyptian God of the [[Moon]] who resided in the temple.
[[File:Moon Knight and Khonshu.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector transforms into Moon Knight]]
Speaking to Spector, Khonshu said that it would be a waste to throw his life away and offered Spector to be his avatar, to punish those who had done evil, stating that he was intrigued by Spector's mental state. Seeing himself as nothing more than a killer, Spector agreed to Khonshu's terms and was granted divine empowerment, allowing him to summon a [[Moon Knight's Suit|ceremonial suit]] as he became the vigilante known as Moon Knight. As Moon Knight, Khonshu used Spector to exact his vengeance on murderers, predators, and other evil-doers, causing Spector to amass a large body count that eventually began to weigh on his conscience. Those victims included [[Dubai Criminal|one]] from [[Dubai]], [[Gabon Criminal|two]] from [[Gabon]] and [[New York Criminal|two]] from [[New York]]. Throughout his servitude to Khonshu, Spector deemed his healing powers a curse, often wishing he would fail and that one of his victims would kill him instead.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Marrying Layla El-Faouly====
{{Quote|I'm sorry."<br>"That's the reason that we met. You just had a guilty conscience.|Marc Spector and [[Layla El-Faouly]]|The Tomb}}
Having a guilty conscience for what happened at the dig site, Spector met [[Abdallah El-Faouly]]'s daughter, [[Layla El-Faouly]], and tried to tell her what happened on the night her father was killed, but could never bring himself to do so.{{Ref|MK104}} Eventually, Spector married El-Faouly, and they went on many adventures to find [[Egypt]]ian relics, such as the [[Scarab of Ammit]]. Spector also informed El-Faouly that he no longer spoke to his parents, specifically his mother, although he did not tell her why. Spector later assumed that [[Khonshu]] was interested in choosing El-Faouly as his new Avatar, and decided to abruptly leave her, leaving unsigned divorce papers to her.{{Ref|MK102}}

====Mother's Funeral====
[[File:MARC SPECTOR.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Spector fails to attend his [[Wendy Spector|mother]]'s {{WPS|Shiva}}]]
{{Quote|No, no. Not gonna do it. I'm not giving [[Wendy Spector|you]] that satisfaction. I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry."<br>"What... [[Chicago|Where]] am I? Bloody hell, what... Oh, bollocks. Not again.|Marc Spector and Steven Grant|Asylum}}
In early [[2025]], Spector was contacted by [[Elias Spector]] for the first time in years, and was told that [[Wendy Spector]] had passed away, asking him to come to her shiva in [[Chicago]]. Spector traveled to Chicago, but stood outside the [[Spector Residence]] drinking alcohol from a hip flask, unable to bring himself to enter his old house. His father noticed Spector from inside and gestured for him to come in, but Spector shook his head before walking away, muttering that he would not give his mother the satisfaction of having him mourn her.
[[File:Marc breaks down.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector breaks down crying in utter agony]]
Despite this, Spector proceeded to have a breakdown over his resurfaced trauma, kneeling on the street and hitting his {{WPS|kippah}} to the ground. He then muttered apologies as he blamed himself for [[Randall Spector]]'s death and cradled his kippah, weeping in psychological pain. Spector could not withstand recalling his childhood memories, so his eyes rolled backwards, allowing Grant to front. Grant was confused as he found himself in an unfamiliar neighborhood.
[[File:Steven Grant talking on the phone.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant supposedly calls his [[Wendy Spector|mother]]]]
He spoke to himself when he believed that he had gotten lost "again," saying the [[England|British]] slang "bollocks." Grant then picked up his phone, thinking that he was calling his mother and told "her" about his current situation, chuckling about how foolish his supposedly was. Continuing to talk while journeying off, Grant described his location as a resemblance to {{WPS|Mayfair}} and noted that the cars were driving on the "wrong side" of the road, believing that he lived in [[London]]. From their mother's death onward, Spector and Grant's lives started intertwining with each other.{{Ref|MK105}}

===Peaceful Life===
====Living as Steven Grant====
{{Quote|I work at a gift shop. Um... My name's Steven Grant.|Steven Grant to [[Arthur Harrow]]|The Goldfish Problem}}
Grant eventually relocated to what he believed was his hometown of [[London]], [[England]] and began doing research on [[Egypt]]ian mythology, ultimately becoming a massive genius in the subject who was qualified enough to educate people. He gained employment as a gift shop worker at the [[National Art Gallery]]. He moved into an [[Steven Grant's Apartment|apartment]] with a pet one-finned {{WPS|goldfish}} named [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]], and during his time at the museum, Grant was often mistreated by his boss [[Donna Kraft]] and neglected by the security guard [[J.B.]] Grant desired to be a tour guide, but Kraft disregarded his hopes.{{Ref|MK101}} This made him often imagine himself killing Kraft out of frustration.{{Ref|MK102}} He also made acquaintances with the street performer posing as a golden living statue [[Bertrand Crawley]], having conversations with him from time to time, though Crawley did not respond to him. Additionally, Grant spent his time as a vegan.

Unbeknownst to Grant, Spector and Lockley would front when he fell asleep to operate as Moon Knight during the night before returning to the apartment, which would leave Grant feeling tired when he woke up. Additionally, Grant would occasionally regain control of the body before Spector could return home, leading Grant to believe that he was suffering from sleepwalking. These strange occurrences led Grant to strap his ankle to a wooden post whenever he went to bed to prevent him from leaving, as well as applying a sand circle around his bed and tape on his door so that he could verify in the morning whether he had left.{{Ref|MK101}}

Spector, however, was aware of Grant's actions and removed the ankle restraint and the tape on the door, as well as avoiding the sand, to continue performing tasks for [[Khonshu]]. When he would return, he would reapply the tape and the restraint in order to prevent Grant from discovering the truth.{{Ref|MK102}} On one occasion, while Lockley was in control, he asked Grant's co-worker [[Dylan]] out for a date to the best steak restaurant in town.<ref>[https://comicbook.com/marvel/news/moon-knight-writer-reveals-who-set-up-the-date/ Moon Knight Writer Reveals Who Set up the Date]</ref>{{Ref|MK101}}

====Steven Grant's New Day====
[[File:Steven Grant First Look.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant wakes up for the day]]
{{Quote|Morning, Gus, my little one-finned wonder.|Steven Grant to [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]]|The Goldfish Problem}}
One morning, Grant woke up from bed in his [[Steven Grant's Apartment|apartment]]. Looking around at first, Grant flipped over his sheets, seeing his ankle restrained to his bedpost. Grant undid his restraint and got out of bed, looking at the sand ring around his bed to see if anyone moved through it. Seeing no new footprints, Grant walked through the ring to the front door, checking if anyone disturbed the tape on the crevasse of the doorframe.
[[File:Gus Turning Right.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant feeds [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]], his pet fish]]
Grant took off the tape and threw it into a nearby trashcan before feeding his pet goldfish [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]]. Grant tried to call his mother [[Wendy Spector]], though he ended up on voicemail. In his ensuing message, Grant mentioned receiving her postcards, placing them on Gus' tank while jokingly claiming that Gus was upset he could not go anywhere special. Grant freshened himself up, mentioning to his mother that he still woke up feeling like he got hit by a bus before leaving his apartment.
[[File:Steven asleep.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant falling asleep on the bus]]
Exiting the apartment building, Grant stopped his voicemail message to briefly comment on an old man still selling his brushes and brooms in front of Grant's doorway. Grant ended his voicemail as he walked down the street, spotting his bus passing by, forcing Grant to give chase. On the bus, Grant was awoken by a man whose backpack he was resting his head on before awkwardly watching a woman read a newspaper, much to her annoyance.{{Ref|MK101}}

====Working at the Art Museum====
[[File:Steven Grant talks about Great Pyramid of Giza.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant talks to a [[List of Minor Characters/Phase Four#The Goldfish Problem|girl]] about the model]]
{{Quote|The [[Ennead]]? You know, like, the super group of [[Egypt]]ian gods? You got [[Horus]], [[Osiris]], [[Tefnut]]..."<br>"Stop, please. If this is some weird audition to tour guide [[National Art Gallery|here]], the answer's still no."<br>"No. What I'm trying... That's actually crushing to hear.|Steven Grant and [[Donna Kraft]]|The Goldfish Problem}}
Grant arrived at his job at the [[National Art Gallery]] late for the third time this week, noticing on the banners outside that there were seven of the [[Ennead]] instead of nine. He then spotting a [[List of Minor Characters/Phase Four#The Goldfish Problem|girl]] in a primary school uniform sticking her discarded chewing gum in a hole on a model of the [[Great Pyramid of Giza]]. The girl responded that there was nothing inside the pyramid, prompting Grant to agree in a way that directed her toward a sarcophagus, though not before removing the gum from the model while she was not looking.
[[File:MK101 - SGrantMuseum.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant talks about the sarcophagus]]
Grant explained that a metal hook would suck out all of the organs of a person inside a sarcophagus apart from their heart, saying that it was left there for judgment in the [[Duat|Underworld]] to see if it was worthy to pass through to the [[Field of Reeds]]. The girl asked if it sucked for Grant to have been rejected himself, though Grant said that would not make sense since he was not dead. Grant slowly began pondering if he truly was dead, as his boss [[Donna Kraft]] got his attention by calling him "Stevie" and asking him to help her carry some boxes over to a counter.
[[File:STEVEN.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant clarifies his name to [[Donna Kraft]]]]
Grant was reprimanded by Kraft for trying to be the tour guide again, calling him "Stevie," though Grant clarified his name as he put on his nametag. Kraft called Grant useless and told him to do his job, to sell gift shop merchandise to children, before walking away, leaving Grant alone to set up a display of items.
[[File:Steven Grant (National Art Gallery).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant is told of a date with [[Dylan]]]]
While he worked, Grant was approached by [[Dylan]], who inquired about how the sugar trade was, and Grant answered that he did not know what it had to do with [[Egypt]] since those snacks did not exist back then. Dylan then questioned if Grant was still available for their steakhouse date tomorrow night at seven. Grant, confused, asked if she was asking him out, much to Dylan's amusement, telling him she would see him later. Kraft, impressed by his apparent date, inquired what a vegan like Grant would eat at a steakhouse. Grant told her that he would eat salad and bread, much to her annoyance as she sarcastically called him a "real catch" and left.
[[File:Steven Grant (Inventory Room).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant points out an error in a banner]]
Grant later began helping Kraft with inventory in the back room, carrying a box of plush toys of [[Taweret]], which reminded himself about an error in the advertisements outside the museum, causing Kraft to ask if that was why he was once again late before telling Grant that he was on inventory duties for the week for being late so often.
[[File:Storeroom (National Art Gallery).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant shuffles out of the room]]
Grant tried to explain that the banner was missing some members of the [[Ennead]], prompting Donna to remark that he wasn't going to be a tour guide if that was what he was trying to do. Briefly heartbroken by this, Grant continued by stating that the Ennead had nine gods rather than seven, though Donna became fed up by him, ordering him to just leave her be. Complying, Grant left the room, fumbling with a poster on the way out.
[[File:MK101 - Steven Grant.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant leaves work for the night]]
At the end of his shift, Grant headed for the exit of the museum, bidding the security guard [[J.B.]] goodnight. J.B. replied back to Grant, calling him "Scotty," much to Grant's bewilderment, who corrected him by stating that that his name was Steven with a "V" in it. Steven then left the museum for the night.{{Ref|MK101}}

====Bonding with Bertrand Crawley====
[[File:MK101 - StevenGrantStatue.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant confides with [[Bertrand Crawley]]]]
{{Quote|What do you think? Nah. You're right. I mean, I guess there are stranger things that people do, but... No? Well, I think it's a bit.|Steven Grant to [[Bertrand Crawley]]|The Goldfish Problem}}
Grant, while eating a snack, met up with [[Bertrand Crawley]], a street performer posing as a golden statue on a bench. Grant confided with Crawley about his constant sleep problems, mentioning he would actively try to stay awake at night to circumvent them before tipping him a package of pralines in his hat. Grant would bring up his upcoming date with Dylan that he did not recall setting up, when a pair of tourists asked Grant to take a picture of them with Crawley.
[[File:Reflection.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant says his farewell to [[Bertrand Crawley]]]]
Grant politely complied to take their picture, reminding them to tip Crawley after taking it. Grant resumed his conversation once the tourists left, saying that if he wanted to have a girlfriend, he would stop having to wear ankle restraints in his bed, noting it was a red flag in a relationship. Finishing his snack, Grant thanked Crawley before bidding him farewell, placing a tip in his hat as he walked away.{{Ref|MK101}}

====Staying Awake====
[[File:Reading books.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant reading books on the [[Ennead]]]]
Returning to his [[Steven Grant's Apartment|apartment]], Grant prepared himself for bed. Grant first filled in the footstep he made in his sand ring around his bed, before placing a piece of tape on the crevasse of his doorway and locking the door firmly shut. Grant then went and studied various books regarding topics related to the [[Ennead]], including the rift between god and man.
[[File:Steven Grant tries to stay awake.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant tries to stay awake]]
Afterwards, he entered bed, where he put his right ankle in a restraint locked to the bedpost. Grant turned on the ''[[Staying Awake]]'' audio program, fiddling aimlessly with a {{WPS|Rubik's Cube}} while lying in bed. While in bed, Grant fell asleep or lost front.{{Ref|MK101}}
{{Clear}}

===Identity Struggle===
====[[Theft of the Scarab of Ammit|Hunting for the Scarab]]====
[[File:Dislocated jaw.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant waking up with his dislocated jaw]]
{{Quote|I will not ask again."<br>"I didn't do that on purpose. I don't know what's happening.|[[Arthur Harrow]] and Steven Grant|The Goldfish Problem}}
Without any warning, Grant suddenly awoke amidst a meadow in the [[Austria|Alps]] of [[Austria]] with a broken jaw. Grant, caught aback by the situation, attempted to fix his jaw, which mysteriously healed nearly instantaneously. Getting up from the ground, Grant looked around in confusion and panic, spotting a nearby village when a voice demanded he go back to sleep, retorting that Grant wasn't supposed to be here.
[[File:Moon Knight Big Game TV Spot (1).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant senses a [[Khonshu|presence]] right behind him]]
Grant agreed with the voice, asking where he was, though the voice only told Grant to surrender his body to Marc, much to Grant's confusion. The voice lamented that "the idiot" was still in control, prompting Grant to feel around his jacket until he uncovered a mysterious [[Scarab of Ammit|scarab]] in his pocket. Looking at the scarab, Grant felt a [[Khonshu|presence]] behind him, and when he turned around, he found himself staring at a castle directly behind him.
[[File:Steven Grant.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant witnesses the guards aiming at him]]
Grant spotted a guard looking down at him from a window higher up. Grant awkwardly waved toward the guard, who returned the gesture. Another guard then peered out of the window with a rifle, admonishing the first guard for his hesitance. The two guards opened fire on Grant, prompting the voice to tell Grant to run.
[[File:Steven Grant hiding.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant trying to hide in an [[Austria|Austrian]] village]]
Running through the meadow, Grant was chased by additional guards on the ground as he then entered the nearby village. Grant narrowly avoided another pair of guards in an alley, before finding himself entering a crowd of people assembling in a nearby square. Grant quickly pulled the hood of his sweatshirt over his head as he passed by another guard, narrowly avoiding detection.
[[File:Moon Knight Promo Spot (21).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant walking into the village square]]
At the square, Grant witnessed the arrival of [[Arthur Harrow]] as the crowd parted for him to walk through. Harrow stood at the front of the crowd at the base of a statue, while Grant watched as he requested people to come up to be judged by the [[Staff of Ammit]] and the tattooed scale on his arm. Grant observed a young man step forward, who was thanked by Harrow for volunteering to be the first, as he was then judged to be a good person.
[[File:Steven Grant meets Arthur Harrow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant observes [[Arthur Harrow]]'s judgement]]
Several guards began to appear from behind the crowd, forcing Grant to enter deeper into the crowd and closer toward Harrow. An older woman stepped forward next for judgement, and Grant watched as she was judged negatively, despite her insistence that she had been good her whole life. Harrow apologized, but informed her of the staff’s ability to judge the future of its victim as well. Then, the woman's life force was absorbed from her body, killing her instantly and shocking Grant as her body was promptly carried away by other followers.
[[File:Standing out from the crowd.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant being outed from inside the crowds]]
A guard informed Harrow that someone interrupted their exchange and that the perpetrator was potentially still nearby. Harrow announced to the crowd in ancient Egyptian, who responded by kneeling, though Grant was outed as a result of his unknowingness to comply. Harrow recognized Grant, calling him a mercenary, though a confused Grant assured him his name was Steven Grant, a gift shopist from [[London]].
[[File:MK101 - SGrant&AHarrow (3).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant attempting to relinquish the [[Scarab of Ammit|scarab]]]]
Harrow requested Grant to hand over the scarab, and though Grant was willing to comply, the voice impeded his attempts to surrender the scarab to Harrow. After several failed attempts to hand over the scarab, Grant was physically forced by the voice to walk away as Harrow ordered his followers to subdue him. Grant was wrestled through the crowd toward a storefront, where a few guards and a shopkeeper ripped the scarab out of his grasp. Grant suddenly found himself blacking out another alter took front, killing his attackers around him.{{Ref|MK101}}

====Chased through the Alps====
[[File:Steven DID.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant regains control around dead [[Disciples of Ammit|disciples]]]]
{{Quote|Wake up, Marc! If he loses the [[Scarab of Ammit|scarab]], I'll kill you both."<br>"I don't understand what's happening!|[[Khonshu]] and Steven Grant|The Goldfish Problem}}
Grant then regained his senses as he stood over the bodies of his [[Disciples of Ammit|attackers]] while the [[Khonshu|voice]] remarked that the idiot was back. Grant realized he now had the scarab back in his blood-soaked hand, and began to run away as [[Arthur Harrow]] and his followers approached him. The voice scolded Grant not to drop the [[Scarab of Ammit]], who complied as he hijacked a parked cupcake delivery van nearby and raced out of the village.
[[File:Steven Grant fleeing.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant fleeing in a cupcake van]]
