[[File:Marc & Layla.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector looks at [[Senfu]]'s sarcophagus]]
Spector and El-Faouly were then led to the sarcophagus and both examined it. However, Spector and El-Faouly were unable to decipher the translations. When Mogart asked them what they wanted there, Spector told El-Faouly he needed time, and she went out to distract them.
[[File:Marc argues with Steven.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector argues with Grant]]
When she had left, Spector spoke to Grant, who told him he wouldn't help since he wasn't in control. Spector urged him to help and ignored Grant's arguments about their deal. Fortunately, Grant gave in and looked at the translations. However, due to the awkward nature of Spector seemingly arguing with himself, Mogart and his men eventually entered.
[[File:Marc Spector surrenders.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector chooses not to fight]]
Spector immediately grabbed a gun off of one of Mogart's men, but gave it up after they had aimed guns at him and El-Faouly. As they stood in Mogart's custody, Mogart told them that they had company. Spector then watched as [[Arthur Harrow]] and his [[Disciples of Ammit|followers]] approached.
[[File:Marc glares at Harrow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector glares at [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
Harrow confronted them, and taunted Spector by speaking to El-Faouly. He told her that Spector was keeping a secret from her that was about her. She looked at Spector, who shook his head, and glared at Harrow. He then watched as Harrow walked up to Mogart and showed him his [[Staff of Ammit]], before revealing its powers, destroying the sarcophagus. Harrow then left them.{{Ref|MK103}}

====[[Battle at Anton Mogart's Estate]]====
[[File:Knight of the night.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight surveys the situation]]
{{Quote|Give me the body, Marc! Oh! Sorry. You all right? That's it. All right, time out. That's it, time out! Guys, let's all calm down, yeah? We're all worked up. Let's all just, like, chill the F out and talk for a second... Take the body. Take the body, take the body, Marc.|Mr. Knight|The Friendly Type}}
Spector, at [[Khonshu]]'s urging, became Moon Knight, and descended from above an upper building to confront [[Anton Mogart]]'s men. They were startled at this and began firing their guns.
[[File:Moon Knight protecting Layla.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight protects [[Layla El-Faouly]]]]
Moon Knight then shielded [[Layla El-Faouly]] within his suit from the gunfire. When he deemed it safe, he let her go, and fought off the men. As she ran out of the arena area, Moon Knight proceeded to engage in a fight with the men.
[[File:Moon Knight fighting goons.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight fighting [[Anton Mogart]]'s men]]
Moon Knight fought them in the arena, coming out victorious. He used his [[Crescent Darts]] on them, kicked and punched them, and broke one man's arm. As more men entered armed with weapons, Moon Knight continued to fight.
[[File:Mr Knight takes over.png|{{AltFloat}}|Mr. Knight attempting to call for a timeout]]
During the fight, Moon Knight suddenly switched to Mr. Knight. He then held his hands up and called for a ceasefire, as Grant didn't want to continue to fight. This was unsuccessful as the men took this to their advantage and impaled him in the back with their jousting sticks.
[[File:Marc Spector (Moon Knight).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight being repeatedly impaled]]
Grant then immediately let Spector take control as Moon Knight. As Moon Knight fought off the men while trying to get the sticks out, he used them to his advantage and struck the men with them, knocking them to the ground. He then snapped the sticks in half and walked away.
[[File:Moon Knight hits Anton Mogart.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight defeating [[Anton Mogart]]]]
Moon Knight then saw El-Faouly enter the arena, and ran to her, as Mogart was attempting to run over both of them on horseback. He ran to her in time and threw a Crescent Blade at Mogart, causing him to fall off his horse and fatally wounding him.{{Ref|MK103}}

====Turning Back the Sky====
[[File:Marc examines jacket.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector riding away with [[Layla El-Faouly]]]]
{{Quote|This is the night."<br>"This is surprisingly painful."<br>"It's working.|[[Khonshu]], Mr. Knight and [[Layla El-Faouly]]|The Friendly Type}}
After escaping, Spector and [[Layla El-Faouly]] escaped into the desert. With El-Faouly driving, Spector changed his shirt for another one. He was pressed on the secret that he had been keeping, but he brushed it aside stating that it was just cause for division. She thought that he had not been telling her everything and he told her not to worry about it, as she didn't need to know everything.
[[File:Marc and Layla working together.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector attempting to assemble the map]]
They stopped in the sands of the [[Siwa Oasis]] and began inspecting the map. As they did, Spector became frustrated and El-Faouly suggested he summon Grant for help. Initially, Spector refused, but gave in and tore the side mirror off, walking away to do so.
[[File:Steven Grant tags in.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant managing to analyses the star map]]
They switched quite easily, and Grant then assembled some of the sarcophagus fragments into a star map, revealing it to be two thousand years out of date. El-Faouly approached him and smiled that he was able to help them.
[[File:Mr. Knight, Khonshu & Layla.png|{{AltFloat}}|Mr. Knight and [[Khonshu]] turn back the sky]]
[[Khonshu]] then appeared and told Grant to follow his lead. Grant was then transformed into Mr. Knight as Khonshu used his powers to briefly turn back the night sky to the correct night, allowing Grant and El-Faouly to pinpoint the location of Ammit's tomb using the constellations. However, Khonshu paid the price for abusing his power and was imprisoned in stone.
[[File:Steven Grant passes out.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant passes out from the exhaustion]]
Due to Khonshu being imprisoned in stone, his powers given to Grant and Spector were stripped away. This impact of losing the superhuman powers had an effect on Grant, who fell to the ground unconscious.{{Ref|MK103}}

====Escaping Harrow====
[[File:Layla and Steven at night.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant witnesses [[Layla El-Faouly]]'s explosion]]
{{Quote|He'd wanna lone wolf this whole thing. It's not happening. We're not gonna do that."<br>"We are not. It's just you and me, and the open road."<br>"We're gonna go on foot from here.|[[Layla El-Faouly]] and Steven Grant|The Tomb}}
Some minutes later, Grant regained consciousness and found [[Layla El-Faouly]] looking at an armored truck that had just exploded by way of flare. Not knowing what had happened, he approached her, and she turned around to see him, dismissing what she had just done to save them.
[[File:Steven Grant passenger.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant rides with [[Layla El-Faouly]]]]
In the morning, they set out again to the location of the [[Tomb of Alexander the Great|tomb]]. As El-Faouly drove them, Grant spoke to Spector from the side mirror, who told him that he remembered their deal about going away once [[Khonshu]] was gone. El-Faouly interjected stating to Grant that she needed to have a voice in the matter since Spector was her husband. Grant then became startled as she stopped the vehicle suddenly as the path had become too narrow ahead.{{Ref|MK104}}

====Finding the Tomb====
[[File:Steven Grant in Egypt.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant sees the empty camp of the [[Disciples of Ammit|Disciples]]]]
{{Quote|I have to say, I feel like I've been waiting for this my whole life. The adventure, I mean."<br>"I know. We want what we never had.|Steven Grant and [[Layla El-Faouly]]|The Tomb}}
Grant and [[Layla El-Faouly]] then walked on foot through the narrow gauge and made it to a larger opening. They found an abandoned campsite that the [[Disciples of Ammit]] had used, along with their {{WPS|camels}}. Grant said hi to one of them as they explored the camp.
[[File:Steven Grant dismisses Marc Spector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant ignores Spector's threats]]
El-Faouly told Grant to look into the tents for anything helpful. As she went in one, he went into another and looked around. When he came across a small mirror, Spector got onto him, telling him that he noticed Grant and El-Faouly's growing affection. He told Grant that she was his wife and that if he did anything, he'd throw their body off a cliff.
[[File:Steven Grant & Layla El-Faouly.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant tells [[Layla El-Faouly]] the secret]]
While preparing their harnesses to descend down, El-Faouly remarked that Grant smelled like Spector and moved in to kiss him. Grant interrupted her by revealing that the reason Spector abandoned her was because [[Khonshu]] threatened to make her his next Avatar. She told him that it wasn't Spector's choice to make.
[[File:Steven Grant kisses Layla El-Faouly.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant kisses [[Layla El-Faouly]]]]
Grant then proceeded to lean in and kiss El-Faouly. She smiled and then as he made a joke, she jumped down. As he looked down, Spector punched him in the face in retaliation for him kissing his wife.{{Ref|MK104}}

====Exploring the Lost Tomb====
[[File:Steven & Layla (The Tomb).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant talks to [[Layla El-Faouly|El-Faouly]] inside the tomb]]
{{Quote|That's [[Macedonia|Macedonian]]. But the only pharaoh... But, I mean, he insisted on calling himself [[Egypt|Egyptian]]. But... I think we're looking at the long-lost tomb of [[Alexander the Great]].|Steven Grant|The Tomb}}
Grant then stumbled and fell into the [[Tomb of Alexander the Great|tomb]]. He approached [[Layla El-Faouly]] and as she spoke about her father, complimented her that he would have been proud of her.
[[File:StevenGrant-MoonKnight.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant deduces where [[Ammit]]'s ushabti is]]
As they walked further into the tomb, Grant deduced that it was built in the shape of the Eye of [[Horus]] and from that figured out where Ammit's ushabti was most likely located.
[[File:The Tomb (24).png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant hides from the [[Heka Priests|Heka Priest]]]]
While moving forward, Grant noticed that a hallway was filled with bones and viscera, and decided to jump on the rafters to look for an alternate route. Before El-Faouly could follow, an undead [[Heka Priests|Heka Priest]] brought [[Billy Fitzgerald]] into the room and sacrificed him, forcing El-Faouly and Grant to run from the creature in separate directions.
[[File:StevenGrant-TheTomb.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant finds [[Alexander the Great]]'s tomb]]
Grant approached the resting place of the pharaoh, and noticed [[Macedonia|Macedonian]] writing, revealing that this was the lost tomb of [[Alexander the Great]]. Grant opened the sarcophagus and, figuring the ushabti would be hidden from looters, reluctantly forced his hand down Alexander's throat to recover the idol.
[[File:Steven holding Ammit's Ushabti.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant holds [[Ammit]]'s ushabti]]
Shortly after the ushabti was recovered, Grant looked at, proud that he had found it before anyone else could. As he prepared to figure out what to do next, he was met El-Faouly. Upon seeing her, he held up the ushabti and told her that they had succeeded.
[[File:I'm talking to you Marc.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is confronted by [[Layla El-Faouly]]]]
El-Faouly ignored this and angrily demanded to speak to Spector. This caused Grant to be confused and for Spector to jump to front, who tried to get El-Faouly to run before the [[Disciples of Ammit]] arrive, but she wouldn't leave until they talked. Eventually, he told El-Faouly the truth about her father [[Abdallah El-Faouly]] and his own role in his death.{{Ref|MK104}}

====Killed by Harrow====
[[File:Marc Spector (The Tomb).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector faces the [[Disciples of Ammit]]]]
{{Quote|I remember the first morning I woke up knowing that [[Khonshu]] was gone. The quiet was liberating. You're a free man. And, of course, with that freedom comes choice. And right now, you have a very important decision to make.|[[Arthur Harrow]] to Marc Spector|The Tomb}}
Before they could continue, [[Arthur Harrow]] and his [[Disciples of Ammit|followers]] came inside. [[Layla El-Faouly]] told Spector to come with her to leave, but he held his ground and told her to go. Knowing that he had no powers, he still tried to fight. He picked up [[Alexander the Great]]'s axe and defeated two men.
[[File:Marc Spector shot in the chest.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is shot by [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
In response, he was shot in the chest twice by Harrow, and stumbled backwards into the water. He looked up at the ceiling as he felt as if he was drowning and couldn't come back to the surface.{{Ref|MK104}}

===Duat===
====Waking Up====
[[File:Falling into the sunken place.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector's soul is brought to the [[Duat]]]]
{{Quote|[[Arthur Harrow|You]] shot me.|Marc Spector to [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]|The Tomb}}
After passing away on the shallow temple pond, Spector's soul began sinking deeper into a dark abyss, still as a lifeless body. Suddenly, he was brought towards a shining, bright, white light that transported him to the [[Duat]], the [[Egypt]]ian underworld. In there, Spector woke up sitting on a wheelchair in the [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]] common room, heavily sedated. He was watching his favourite film ''[[Tomb Buster]]'' on the television before his wheelchair was pulled away by [[Billy Fitzgerald/Duat|Billy Fitzgerald]].
[[File:Goldfish (Putnam Psychiatric Hospital).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector finds himself in the [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]]]]
This gave Spector an opportunity to observe his surroundings, where he watched [[Bertrand Crawley/Duat|Bertrand Crawley]] hosting a bingo game, with some of the patients playing included recreated people he knew, such as [[Donna Kraft/Duat|Donna Kraft]]. The orderlies also consisted of [[Bobbi Kennedy/Duat|Bobbi Kennedy]] and [[Bek/Duat|Bek]], with the latter complimenting a patient's drawing that resembled [[Khonshu]]. Finally, Spector was placed in front of a translucent window with bars outside, and he could almost see his reflection. Notably, a [[Fish|goldfish]] resembling [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]] was set near him. 
[[File:Marc Layla.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector sees [[Layla El-Faouly/Duat|Layla El-Faouly]] playing bingo]]
Fitzgerald pulled on the brakes on Spector's chair and calmly assured to him that he was at his favourite spot. The struggling Spector was then approached by [[Layla El-Faouly/Duat|Layla El-Faouly]], who was also a patient in the hospital. El-Faouly told him that she changed the movie for the fifth time this week while pasting photos and drawings themed with Egyptian mythology on a whiteboard. Spector, confused, tried to speak, but he only moaned, making El-Faouly think she startled him. She then noticed on the bingo paper on Spector's lap that they had an I-2 as announced by Crawley, making them the winners.
[[File:Moon Knight Promo Spot (46).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector falls to the floor]]
After El-Faouly left swearing that she would share the prize with him, he noticed his reflection. Spector looked at his reflection and tried to call out for Grant, but he was not present. He attempted to walk towards the window, but the ankle restraint to the chair caused him to fall to the ground. Fitzgerald helped carry Spector back onto the wheelchair, saying that he cannot keep doing this, and a bewildered Spector found that he himself had dropped an action figure that was designed almost exactly like [[Moon Knight's Suit]].
[[File:Marc sedated.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector meets Doctor [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
After the sedation began to wear off again, Spector was sent to the office of Doctor [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]], a psychiatrist who reassured him that he was aware of Spector's supposed difficulty in differentiating reality and his imagination, implying that everything he experienced as Khonshu's Avatar was all a delusion. Harrow showed him his copy of ''Tomb Buster'', while Spector's vision was a blur. As the therapist continued to complement the movie, Spector distinguished his surroundings. He did not answer Harrow when he asked about the similarity between the lunar god theme in the film and Spector's statement to have served one.
[[File:Marc Spector (Arthur Harrow's Office).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector has therapy with [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Spector's vision finally cleared up, and he tried say that someone might have sedated him, but Harrow responded that he was in this state due to his behavior, but the effects would wear off. While Harrow explained his philosophy about living in a psychic world, Spector took glances at Harrow's cane, a reflection of Harrow's shoes in a mirror and a fly on his hand. He uttered an attempt to say that everything reminded him of the living world, though Harrow assumed he meant his past and Steven Grant, the mention of his name surprising Spector.
[[File:You shot me...png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is frightened of [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
He did not listen to Harrow's statement about their sessions where he was often agitated by direct questions, since he stared at a miniature sculpture resembling [[Ammit]], a painting of the Alps of [[Austria]], Harrow's face, a glass lanky pyramid, the ''Tomb Buster'' copy, Harrow's cane and reflection of his shoes. When Harrow told him that he could not help him if he did not help himself, something similar to the real [[Arthur Harrow]]'s last words to him, Spector recollected his thoughts and mistook Doctor Harrow for the actual one, saying that he shot him.
[[File:Marc drooling.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector tries to escape [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Frightened and panicked, Spector repeated his words and tried to stand up, but he fell to the ground due to the sedatives, drooling. He ignored Harrow's pleas to calm down and crawled away, noticing ancient Egyptian themed items and shouting at Harrow to stay away. When he stood up again, he felt drowsy and collapsed before continuing to stumble to the door. Spector desperately tried to use the knob and demanded the sympathizing Harrow to unlock the door.
[[File:Marc runs through the hospital.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector runs through the [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]]]]
He then broke the window on the door with his elbow and exited the room, only to be grabbed back inside by Fitzgerald and Kennedy. Spector punched Fitzgerald in the stomach and bit Kennedy's hand, allowing him to run outside. Sprinting through the hallways with hardly any effect from the sedatives, Spector turned another corner to see the place rocking sideways and Egyptian-reminiscent lanterns flickering momentarily. He shook his head and ran once more, finding a room to hide in as the two orderlies passed Spector's spot.{{Ref|MK104}}

====Split Alters====
[[File:Steven Grant and Marc Spector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector finds Grant separated from him]]
{{Quote|How is this possible?"<br>"I don't know.|Steven Grant and Marc Spector|The Tomb}}
Inside the room, Spector noticed a blue sarcophagus and heard someone inside trying to get out and screaming for help. Spector proceeded to remove the casket to reveal a horrified, physical form of Grant, separated from his body. Grant breathed heavily and frantically climbed out, and as soon as they met eyes, the two overjoyed alters embraced each other. They were both appalled by the current situation, and Grant questioned how they were possibly separated.
[[File:Steven Grant Marc Spector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant and Spector run into [[Taweret]]]]
Spector was joyous when Grant confirmed that the last thing he remembered was [[Arthur Harrow]] shooting them, and Spector led the puzzled Grant outside the room. Spector walked somewhat stealthily and they noticed in another room a red sarcophagus with the person inside silent yet trying to push the casket open. Unbeknownst to Spector and Grant, that person was Lockley, their mysterious third alter. The pair ignored it and steadily approached the doors, until a shadowing figure was visible through the opaque door window. The doors opened to reveal [[Taweret]], who lightheartedly greeted them, but they screamed at the top of their lungs in fear, with Grant grabbing onto a trolley of towels.{{Ref|MK104}}
[[File:Marc Spector Asylum (2).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector appears in [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]'s office]]
Suddenly, the screaming Spector, who had a bruised face, found himself sitting in Doctor [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]'s office. He was told that he did not shoot Spector, but rather his mind was oscillating between sense and nonsense. Harrow elaborated that he was supposedly switching between the "reality" that he was a patient in [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]] and a "fantasy" where he was a superhero. Spector accused Harrow of not really being a doctor, and Harrow asked if that was why he kept starting imaginary fights in the hospital.
[[File:Marc Spector Asylum (4).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is questioned by [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Harrow began question about Spector, inquiring how he arrived here, but Spector turned the question the other way around and asked Harrow how he got here, to which he answered that he rode a bus. The therapist explained that, according to Spector, he was somewhere oddly reminiscent of the office, except he was in [[Egypt]] and that he was with a rhinoceros, but Spector clarified that it was a talking hippopotamus, referring to Taweret. Spector was then asked if that sounded like sense or nonsense, and he answered nonsense as a question.
[[File:Marc Spector Asylum (5).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector speaks with [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Spector listened to Harrow admitting how he find this encouraging, how Spector's struggling mind would build shelter for different aspects of himself from his most traumatic memories. He gave examples such as a castle, maze or library, and Spector added a psychiatric ward, determining that the ward he was in was an organizing principle. Harrow took interest in Taweret as she could help Spector and Grant open up to each other, then he and the hospital would finally understand what Spector was talking about when he mentioned a little boy in an implied previous session.
[[File:Asylum (1).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector prepares to stab [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Spector deducted that he was referring to [[Randall Spector]], prompting him to lean forward with conflicted expression and thank him. He claimed to have felt really great before grabbing the sharp, glass, lanky pyramid figure and praised how the hospital must have been paying a lot of money, declaring how he supposedly felt like a million dollars. He pretended to try and leave, but then he was grabbed by [[Billy Fitzgerald/Duat|Billy Fitzgerald]] and [[Bobbi Kennedy/Duat|Bobbi Kennedy]].
[[File:Asylum (3).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is stopped from stabbing [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]]]
Spector thrashed around in their grasps as he tried to direct the object to Harrow, yelling he was not a real doctor and that he was going to release [[Ammit]] and destroy everything. While Harrow tried to assure Spector that he was not his enemy, Spector did not relent until he was injected in the neck with another sedative by Kennedy, driving him to yell out as he began to lose consciousness.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Meeting Taweret====
[[File:Marc Spector meets Taweret.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector and Grant meet [[Taweret]]]]
{{Quote|I'll prove it you. So, like, right through these doors, for example, we go through here, there's gonna be patients, and there's [[Bertrand Crawley/Duat|Crawley]] probably about to yell bingo! Oh, my God! Oh, my God!|Marc Spector to Steven Grant|Asylum}}
At that moment, Spector was sent back to the hallway with Grant, both screaming in fear at [[Taweret]]. By the time they settled, Spector called the medicine amazing. Grant confirmed Taweret's question if Spector was always so intense, and when she asked if they were twins, Spector denied it, but Grant verified it to be sort of correct. Spector mentioned that he thought he had been shot to death, so the cheery Taweret clarified that they were actually dead, much to their surprise.
[[File:Marc Spector and Taweret.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector asks about the [[Duat]]]]
They watched as Taweret opened a parcel with a speech, welcoming them as gentle travelers to the [[Duat]], which Grant recognized out loud as the [[Egypt]]ian underworld. He elaborated to Spector as to who Taweret is, the goddess of women and children who would guide them to the afterlife, astounding Grant. Spector then asked if the [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]] was the afterlife, but Taweret explained that this was one of the afterlives, mentioning the [[Ancestral Plane]] as an example. While Taweret tried to find the words in her parcels to say, Spector was struggling to process he was deceased.
[[File:Marc Spector Asylum (7).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector calls himself and Grant insane]]
Taweret spelled out how the Duat reshapes a [[human]] soul's view of the realm into something more recognizable, commenting that this was the first time she had seen it as a psychiatric ward. Grant questioned why they were seeing an asylum, to which Spector answered that they were insane. He believed they were merely insane, since he was seeing a talking hippopotamus, a [[Khonshu|talking dead bird]], Grant was outside his body, and now they were in the afterlife.
[[File:Marc Spector screaming.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector gets shocked by the [[Duat]]]]
Spector began to accept Doctor [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Arthur Harrow]]'s diagnosis that he was delusional, catching Grant's curiosity as to whether [[Arthur Harrow]] was a doctor now. Ignoring Grant calling for him, Spector stated that he would enter the common room where there were a bunch of patients and [[Bertrand Crawley/Duat|Bertrand Crawley]] probably going to yell "bingo," but when he opened the doors, he found himself on top of [[Taweret's Boat]] sailing across the sands of the Duat, much to his utter shock.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Exploring the Past====
[[File:Marc & Steven lose their hearts.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Taweret]] takes Spector and Grant's hearts]]
{{Quote|Marc, all those horrible things that [[Wendy Spector|she]] said to you, she was wrong. It wasn't your fault."<br>"I sh... I shouldn't have brought [[Randall Spector|him]] in that cave. I shouldn't have brought him in the cave."<br>"Hey. Hey. You were just a child. It wasn't your fault.|Steven Grant and Marc Spector|Asylum}}
Grant told the agape Spector that they were in the [[Duat]], the underworld. Spector rejoiced that he was not insane, but Grant was disturbed by the fact he was dead. Grant continued to explain to Spector they were sailing to [[Aaru]], earning a compliment from [[Taweret]] for being "the smart one." After Taweret lectured that they would transcend to Aaru if their hearts were balanced, she then carefully phased her hand through their chests to remove their white hearts, surprising the pair.
[[File:Marc & Steven (Duat).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector and Grant on the Egyptian ship]]
Taweret remarked how she was nervous to accidentally blow up their chests, concerning Grant. Spector was informed by his alter about how Taweret would balance their hearts on the [[Scales of Justice]] and the [[Feather of Truth]], and if their scales balanced, they would be sent to Aaru. However, the scales began fluctuating wildly. Taweret told the pair to travel through the Duat and reconcile their past before they reached the afterlife, or else they would be condemned to the sands of the Duat for all eternity.
[[File:People Marc Spector has killed.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector surrounded by all of his victims]]
They returned to the interior, the doors of which now contained memories from Spector and Grant's life. Spector attempted to convince Grant to help him kill Taweret and steer the boat themselves, but Grant refused. Grant followed a child's voice to the hospital cafeteria, which was filled with the bodies of all the people Spector had killed as Moon Knight. Even though he assured Grant that they were all criminals, he remembered each and every one of them.
[[File:Marc, Randall and Steven.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant watches Randall and Marc]]
Grant then saw a child at the end of the room, who he followed into another door, locking Spector outside. Inside the room, he relived the memories of his brother [[Randall Spector]] drowning and his mother [[Wendy Spector]] becoming abusive. Before he could enter his childhood room, Spector pulled Grant into a new memory of Spector leaving his house as a teenager then his memory of becoming Moon Knight.
[[File:Taweret redirects the ship.png|{{AltFloat}}|Taweret attempts to redirect the ship]]
The duo were suddenly startled by the sound of baboons, and followed them back to the deck of the ship. Taweret watched in horror as souls began pouring into the Duat without being judged, revealing that [[Ammit]] had returned. Spector asked Taweret to return them to life to stop Harrow, but she told him that even if she resurrected them, they would die again of their wounds without [[Khonshu]]'s healing. Spector asked Taweret to send a message to [[Layla El-Faouly]] to free Khonshu, and she agreed to steer the ship towards the realm of the living so long as their scales were balanced.
[[File:Dr. Harrow speaks to Marc.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector is advised by [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Dr. Harrow]]]]
Returning to the interior, Spector refused to let Grant see what was behind that door in his room, eventually breaking down and pounding on his head. He suddenly found himself back in [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Dr. Harrow's]] office, who informed Spector that he had not been injected with anything. Harrow told Spector that he needed to reconcile with Grant.
[[File:My mum is dead.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant tearfully says, "My mum is dead."]]
Finding himself back in the Duat, Spector and Grant entered the room, where Grant witnessed a moment that either caused his split or was very common for them. As his mother broke into the room, Spector pulled Grant away before he could see her beating him. Spector told Grant that he had let Grant live a happy life believing that his mother loved him and was still alive. Grant was incredulous that his mother was dead, but he suddenly appeared in Dr. Harrow's office with a start. Harrow said he was happy to see Grant, since he was worried he would never see him again. Harrow offered to call Grant's mother on the phone, while Grant tried to think of excuses to make him stop. Finally, Grant accepted that his mother was dead after hearing nothing on the line, but a dial tone.
[[File:Steven comforts Marc.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant reassures Spector it was not his fault]]
The two watched one final memory, of Spector refusing to attend his mother's shiva. Grant reassured Spector that it was not his fault that Randall died, and the two hugged before they suddenly felt the boat stop.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Fight in the Duat====
[[File:Egyptian Underworld (6).png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector fighting against the lost souls]]
{{Quote|Marc, you've got this. But if I'm you... It means I've got this, too.|Steven Grant|Asylum}}
Once Grant had noticed that the ship had stopped, Spector and Grant ran back to [[Taweret]]. She informed them that the [[Scales of Justice]] have not balanced, and now the lost souls would be coming to claim their soul. She sadly told them that she was rooting for them, but there was nothing she could do now. Spector and Grant watched on, as the lost souls started boarding their ship. Spector desperately attempted to fend off the intruders, but was losing and was pushed against the railing of the ship.
[[File:Steven Grant death.png|{{AltFloat}}|Grant falls overboard and dies in the [[Duat]]]]
Scared, Grant attempted to assist his alter by turning the ship's wheel, briefly giving Spector some room. However, it was short-lived, as the latter was hit over the head with a metal pole, stunning him. Giving himself a confidence boost, Grant attacked the souls with the metal pole, pulling them off Spector and beating them to death. Spector looked at Grant awestruck, but was then immediately attacked again by an attacker hanging off the ship. Attempting to help Spector, Grant rushed the soul, but he was inadvertently dragged off along with the soul. Spector immediately got up and told Taweret to stop the ship, but was unable, and watched on helplessly, as Grant fell over and slowly turned to sand.{{Ref|MK105}}

====Return to Life====
[[File:Spector in the Field of Reeds.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector arrives at the [[Field of Reeds]]]]
{{Quote|The [[Scales of Justice|scales]] are balanced.|[[Taweret]] to Marc Spector|Asylum}}
In the wake of [[Steven Grant (disambiguation)|Steven Grant]]'s sacrifice, [[Marc Spector]]'s scales had finally balanced against the [[Scales of Justice]] making him worthy to enter into the [[Field of Reeds]], an afterlife of [[Aaru]]. This made Spector transport from the ship into the beautiful dimension at the last moment, as he peered out into the fields in complete awe of the beauty of the place, yet feeling tremendous grief for the loss of his comforting alter.{{Ref|MK105}}

====[[Escape from the Duat|Resurrection]]====
[[File:Hugging in the Underworld.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Spector and Grant hugging each other]]
{{Quote|How's this deal gonna work?"<br>"You would negotiate now, with so much at stake?"<br>"Well, we did learn from the best, you silly old bird."<br>"I will release you both. You have my word.|Mr. Knight and [[Khonshu]]|Gods and Monsters}}
Spector, still saddened by Grant's death, refused to accept peace in the [[Aaru|Field of Reeds]], and left to save Grant, despite [[Taweret]]'s warning that he would not be able to return. Spector found Grant's frozen body, and said to him that he was the only superpower he had. He gave him his heart before he was frozen as well, but both were saved when the [[Gates of Osiris]] were opened. They both hugged each other, but they noticed a sandstorm coming towards them, running towards the gates. Before they get trapped in the sandstorm, Taweret saved them from being consumed. They finally reached the gates and returned to life, though their body was weak due to the bullet holes.
[[File:Moon Knight (Tomb of Alexander the Great).png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight is resurrected]]
[[Khonshu]] detected Spector and Grant's presence in the living world and struck a new agreement, repairing their body and resurrecting Moon Knight. Spector and Grant requested that their agreement be reviewed, stating that they were free to leave once [[Ammit]] was no longer a threat. Khonshu was shocked that they were willing to bargain at that moment, but he had no choice, and accepted their terms.{{Ref|MK106}}

===Battle of the Gods===
====[[Battle of Giza|Final Battle with Harrow]]====
[[File:Moon Knight Moon Fight.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight fighting against [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
{{Quote|That wasn't you, was it, Steven?"<br>"Not a chance, mate.|Marc Spector and Steven Grant|Gods and Monsters}}
[[Arthur Harrow]] sent his newly-granted armies into Cairo, while his disciples evaluated the inhabitants and sent the souls of the unworthy to [[Ammit]] to eat. Grant let Spector take reign as he could fly. Moon Knight made his way to the [[Great Pyramid of Giza]] and landed at the bottom. He ran up to Harrow and leaped, starting a fight.
[[File:Moon Knight vs. Arthur Harrow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight attacked by [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
Spector flew off into the night as Harrow held onto him. Spector then smartly changed to Grant, who did not have a cape, causing them to fall and Harrow to lose his grip. Once that happened, Spector took reign once again, but Harrow managed to grab back on, making them plunge into the street below. The two fought until Spector was overwhelmed by Harrow, who stood over him and was about to finish him off, using his [[Staff of Ammit]].
[[File:Scarlet Scarab and MK.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight alongside [[Scarlet Scarab]]]]
Suddenly, [[Layla El-Faouly]] arrived and saved Spector, knocking Harrow far away from them. The two were overjoyed to see each other alive and well. Grant then surfaced and complimented El-Faouly on her new look, and they both resumed the fight with Harrow and his followers. Grant switched alters to catch Harrow off guard, attacking from multiple sides. Grant knocked Harrow down and neatened his clothing before kicking. Harrow then tackled Grant. At one point, Spector and El-Faouly managed to pin Harrow to a wall, but he managed to break free from them.
[[File:Arthur Harrow vs. Moon Knight.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight almost killed by [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
Harrow eventually was able to overpower Spector as El-Faouly became stuck to a van. Harrow plunged his staff into Spector's chest when Spector suddenly blacked out. Lockley then emerged and plowed through all of the enemies, eventually beating up Harrow. Just before chopping off Harrow's head, he changed back into Spector, who saw the destruction, asking Grant if he did it, but Grant assured him that he was not responsible for the extreme violence. El-Faouly asked what just happened, but Spector had no idea.{{Ref|MK106}}

====Refusing to Kill Harrow====
[[File:Moon Knight grips Crescent Dart.png|{{AltFloat}}|Moon Knight decides not to kill [[Arthur Harrow]]]]
{{Quote|You want them dead... Do it yourself.|Marc Spector to [[Khonshu]]|Gods and Monsters}}
They then brought [[Arthur Harrow]] to the Chamber of the Gods, Spector and [[Layla El-Faouly]] recited an old magic spell to confine [[Ammit]] inside Harrow's body. [[Khonshu]] instructed Spector to kill Harrow so that the two of them are no longer a threat, but Spector refused, claiming that Khonshu and Ammit are nearly identical and asked the moon god to kill Harrow himself. Khonshu agreed with Spector's order and had to keep his end of the bargain by releasing Spector and Grant in exchange for losing their service to the former.
[[File:Marc Spector and Dr. Harrow.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Spector and Grant reject [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Dr. Harrow]]]]
Grant found himself back at the [[Putnam Psychiatric Hospital]]. He asked [[Arthur Harrow/Duat|Dr. Harrow]] if this was what reality looked like. Dr. Harrow reassured Grant who then asked if Harrow believed in [[Khonshu]] and [[Ammit]] to which Dr. Harrow said that he did not. Spector then emerged and asked why they cannot believe different things. Harrow responded that their work had to continue. The men switched back and forth between Grant and Spector. As they sat down, they both noticed that Dr. Harrow was leaving bloody footsteps when walking. Harrow noticed as well and was confused as to why he was bleeding. Grant got up from the chair, telling Harrow that he did not know as much as he thought he did. Spector said that although Harrow's offer was tempting, they would rather save the world. They then fell back and were freed from the [[Duat]].{{Ref|MK106}}

===A Third Alter===
====Back to London====
[[File:Steven Wakes Up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Spector wakes up in Grant's bed]]
{{Quote|I can't believe you live in this fricking mess.|Marc Spector to Steven Grant|Gods and Monsters}}
Waking up in Grant's bed, Spector asked Grant if he was there. Grant confirmed his presence to Spector. While Spector was getting out of bed, he told Grant he could not believe that he lived in the apartment, calling it a dump, before accidentally tripping on the foot restraint and landing on his face.{{Ref|MK106}}

====[[Assassination of Arthur Harrow]]====
[[File:Jake Finds Harrow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lockley finds [[Arthur Harrow]] and takes him]]
{{Quote|Hoy te toca perder.<ref>Translates from Spanish to: "''Today is your turn to lose.''"</ref>|Jake Lockley to [[Arthur Harrow]]|Gods and Monsters}}
Sometime later, Lockley retook control of the body and tracked down Arthur Harrow to the [[Sienkiewicz Psychiatric Hospital]] in London. Lockley traveled to the hospital and killed some of the staff there. After finding Harrow, Lockley, keeping out of Harrow's sight took his wheelchair with Harrow in it from an orderly, saying that he had him. Confused, the orderly asked what he had meant, but Lockley told her to calm down, before escorting Harrow outside the hospital.
[[File:Jake Lockley.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lockley killing [[Arthur Harrow]] inside his car]]
Reaching his limousine parked outside, Lockley shoved Harrow in the backseat and kicked aside his wheelchair, leaving Harrow to speak to Khonshu, as Lockley waited in the front seat. After Khonshu told Harrow that he never wanted El-Faouly as Spector's replacement, but instead he wanted Lockley, so that he could still have Spector under his command. Rolling down the visor blocking Harrow's view, Lockley revealed himself to the shocked Harrow. Lockley told Harrow that it was his turn to lose, pulling out a gun and aiming it at Harrow. Harrow vainly tried to stop Lockley from killing him, but Lockley, with a smile, proceeded to mercilessly shoot Harrow multiple times, killing him and Ammit for good. With his mission finished, Lockley proceeded to drive him and Khonshu away from the hospital.{{Ref|MK106}}

==Powers and Abilities==
{{Expand}}
===Powers===
{{Quote|Then rise. Rise and live again. As my fist of vengeance. As my Moon Knight.|[[Khonshu]] to Marc Spector|Asylum}}
*'''Divine Empowerment''': As the Avatar of [[Khonshu]], Spector and Grant were able to achieve many superhuman feats as Moon Knight and Mr. Knight respectively. However, when Khonshu was imprisoned in stone, he was unable to access his powers until Khonshu was rescued. Even though Spector and Grant were released from servitude, Lockley continues to operate as Khonshu's Avatar.
**'''Transformation''': [[File:Marc Spector becomes Moon Knight.png|thumb|250px|Spector transforming into Moon Knight]] Spector and Grant were able to summon a [[Moon Knight's Suit|suit]] of ceremonial armor over themselves. The suit's appearance can be altered, as Grant manifested it as a business suit by mistake, resulting in it assuming this form thereafter when Grant summons it.
***'''Superhuman Strength''': Moon Knight has superhuman levels of physical strength, numerous times stronger than any normal human being. His strength allows him to physically overpower highly trained humans and even [[Jackals]] with ease. During the [[Ambush on Steven Grant]], Moon Knight was able to easily overpower a jackal, strong enough to drag it back into the bathroom when it attempted to escape and then beat it to death with only a few hits. During the [[Kidnapping of Steven Grant]], Mr. Knight was able to dent a car bumper when he squeezed it tight and pull it out from the car with ease, and punch a jackal several meters away. Moon Knight was able to effortlessly lift up a jackal while falling down from a building, and implant it on a steeple, killing it instantly. When Mogart's henchmen riddled his cape with bullets, Moon Knight returned them with force and accuracy by flourishing his cape in their direction. He was able to send one man flying with a punch, as well as break other men's arms and legs with ease. He also quickly broke free of the spears impaled into him.
***'''Superhuman Durability''': [[File:Moon Knight withstanding energy blasts.png|thumb|250px|Moon Knight withstanding energy blasts]] Moon Knight has superhuman levels of durability, making him extremely resistant to physical and energy damage, as well as completely bulletproof. During the [[Ambush on Steven Grant]], Moon Knight was able to easily withstand a charge attack from a jackal with no injuries. During the [[Kidnapping of Steven Grant]], Mr. Knight was able to land on his feet after falling down several stories and withstand a jackal falling several stories down onto him without any injury. He was also able to withstand being thrown several meters onto the road while crashing through a gate by a jackal, and repeatedly kicked, dragged, choked, slammed or thrown onto a car and a bus with considerable force, and directly hit in the head with a car wheel by a jackal, all without any noticeable injury. In addition, Mr. Knight was able to withstand a car crashing onto him at high speed without injury. Moon Knight was able to withstand falling down several stories with no injuries after killing a jackal by implanting it on a steeple.
***'''Superhuman Speed''': Moon Knight has superhuman levels of speed, allowing him to run and move at incredible speeds and even outrun [[Jackals]]. During the [[Kidnapping of Steven Grant]], Moon Knight was able to outpace a jackal that was chasing him with ease, running extremely fast across rooftops in order to best the fast creature.
***'''Superhuman Agility''': [[File:Knight of the Moon.png|thumb|250px|Moon Knight leaps across building rooftops]] Moon Knight has superhuman levels of agility, allowing him to coordinate his body with perfect balance, equilibrium, flexibility, and dexterity, as well as leaping great distances and heights with precision, and easily capable of jumping and leaping from one building to another. During the [[Kidnapping of Steven Grant]], Moon Knight was able to easily jump and leap to a height of several stories and scale the wall with ease. Moon Knight was also able to effortlessly leap several meters from one building to another while running across rooftops and performing acrobatic moves in between them, easily outmaneuvering a jackal who was chasing him.
***'''Superhuman Endurance''': Moon Knight demonstrated an advanced tolerance for pain and injury, allowing Spector to continue fighting while impaled by multiple spears. Despite their shared body’s resilience, Grant was still unable to handle the pain and ceded control over to Spector.
***'''Superhuman Stamina''': Moon Knight was able to scale buildings and jump across rooftops while chasing the jackal, without being worn out or tired. He performed many acrobatic moves while jumping from building to building, also without showing any sign of needing to stop.
***'''Superhuman Reflexes''': [[File:Mr Knight agility.png|thumb|250px|Mr. Knight dodging an energy blast]] Moon Knight can react and dodge attacks or objects traveling at high speeds.
***'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': Spector is able to heal from any external wounds he's received, even when he was not Moon Knight. Grant was able to heal his jaw very quickly when it was knocked out of place. However, his healing factor is tremendously increased upon wearing the suit. He was able to immediately heal himself after being impaled by several spears.
***'''Supernatural Perception''': Moon Knight is able to see supernatural phenomenon that cannot be perceived by the human eye; he was able to see a jackal that was chasing him even when a security camera could not.
***'''Flight''': During the [[Battle of Giza]], Moon Knight was able to fly to the pyramids to stop [[Arthur Harrow]] from killing more people. However, only Spector has this ability as he utilizes his cape to do so.
***'''Weapon Summoning''': Whenever summoning the ceremonial armor as Moon Knight or Mr. Knight, the transformation also allows for the conjuration of weapons such as [[Crescent Darts]] or [[Mr. Knight's Truncheons|truncheons]], with the former demonstrating the ability to return to Moon Knight's hand after being thrown.
***'''Power Augmentation''': [[File:Moon Knight Promo Spot (4).png|thumb|250px|Mr. Knight changing the night sky]] With the help of Khonshu and other avatars of the Ennead such as [[Scarlet Scarab]], Grant was able to be empowered by [[Khonshu]] in order to alter the sky to how it was 2,000 years ago and Grant and Spector were able to imprison [[Ammit]] within the body of [[Arthur Harrow]].
****'''Sky Manipulation''': Mr. Knight, with the help of [[Khonshu]], was able to alter the night sky to reveal what the stars had looked like 2,000 years ago. Doing this comes at a price, however, as the other gods disapproved and banished [[Khonshu]], due to the stars changing being visible to everyone, not just Mr. Knight. When he alters the night sky, the stars appear to be spinning so fast they become blurred lines.
****'''Deity Imprisonment''': [[File:Moon Knight and Scarlet Scarab trap Ammit in Arthur Harrow's body.png|thumb|250px|Moon Knight traps [[Ammit]] in [[Arthur Harrow|Harrow]]'s body]] With a spell, Moon Knight and [[Layla El-Faouly|Scarlet Scarab]] were able to imprison [[Ammit]] inside of [[Arthur Harrow]]'s body.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|I am the god Khonshu, in search of a warrior. To be my hands, my eyes, my vengeance. To be my final word against the evildoers. To bind your very being to me and eradicate only the worst, those who deserve it.|[[Khonshu]] to Marc Spector|Asylum}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Moon Knight vs. Arthur Harrow.jpg|thumb|250px|Moon Knight fighting against [[Arthur Harrow]]]] Spector is an extremely skilled and formidable hand-to-hand combatant and martial artist, having trained in the [[United States Marine Corps|Marine Corps]]. He was chosen to be a warrior by [[Khonshu]], who deemed him to be "a worthy candidate." As Moon Knight, he brutally subdued a jackal creature in the museum restroom. He later took on several [[Disciples of Ammit]] and defeated Anton Mogart's men. His fighting style includes Boxing, Krav-Maga, Jiu-jitsu, Wrestling, Taekwondo, Karate, Kung Fu, Kali, Escrima, and Muay Thai. Grant later displayed some combat mastery during the [[Battle of Giza]].
*'''Knife Mastery''': Spector is extremely skilled at using knives in combat, demonstrated when he took on several knife wielding followers of Ammit. This skill also extends to using his [[Crescent Darts]] as melee weapons and throwing weapons. His third alter, Jake Lockley, is also proficient with a knife.
{{Quote|Hey, I'm really jazzed about showing you these new skillsets we have."<br>"All right, show me what you got.|Steven Grant and [[Layla El-Faouly]]|Gods and Monsters}}
*'''Staff Mastery''': [[File:Mr. Knight fighting (3).png|thumb|250px|Mr. Knight fighting [[Disciples of Ammit|disciples]] with his staffs]] Grant is innately skilled with using stick-type weapons in combat, as his Mr. Knight armor is equipped with truncheons rather than crescent blades. He was able to take down Harrow's disciples alongside Layla with his truncheons. In the [[Duat]], he used a baseball bat to kill three souls and save Spector.
*'''Spear Mastery''': Spector is highly skilled at using a spear in combat, being able to use a broken El-Mermah stick to fight and kill three of [[Anton Mogart]]'s security guards at once.
*'''Axe Mastery''': Spector is highly skilled at using an axe in combat, demonstrated when he took on three armed men within a few seconds. He is also skilled at throwing them with great accuracy. While Spector and Grant blacked out, Lockley also briefly used Harrow's [[Staff of Ammit]] against him, before Spector took back control.
*'''Master Marksman''': As a mercenary, Spector is highly proficient with pistols, as well as Jake Lockley, who executed [[Arthur Harrow]] with a silenced pistol. Spector is also capable of throwing his crescent blades with great precision and can even throw multiple of them simultaneously. He managed to hit [[Anton Mogart]] with one of his crescent blades as the latter was escaping on horseback.
*'''Master Acrobat''': [[File:Moon Knight lunges.png|thumb|250px|Moon Knight swiftly traversing rooftops]] Spector is highly skilled in parkour and freerunning, as demonstrated when he led a jackal away from the public by traversing rooftops.
{{Quote|So, what? Am I, like, meant to be some sort of mad secret agent or something?|Steven Grant to Marc Spector|Summon the Suit}}
*'''Master Spy''': Spector is a secret agent and is thus highly skilled with spycraft.
{{Quote|You killed all of them?"<br>"They were criminals. Murderers. Predators. The worst of the worst.|Steven Grant and Marc Spector|Asylum}}
*'''Master Assassin''': [[File:Moon Knight Fights Thugs.jpg|thumb|250px|Moon Knight kills [[Anton Mogart]]'s guards]] As a global mercenary, Spector is a highly skilled assassin, with him killing many members of [[Disciples of Ammit]] in the Alps and [[Anton Mogart]]'s security guards in [[Cairo]]. He has killed all over the world, from [[Dubai]] to [[Gabon]] to [[New York City]].{{Ref|MK105}} Spector's alter, Jake Lockley, is a cold-blooded killer, having executed [[Arthur Harrow]] while Spector declined to do so, along with killing several staff members of the [[Sienkiewicz Psychiatric Hospital]] without being noticed.
{{Quote|Marc, we need Steven. He understands all of this. I really think it's worth giving him a shot.|[[Layla El-Faouly]] to Marc Spector|The Friendly Type}}
*'''Gifted Intellect''': Spector and Grant are two highly intelligent men, with Spector specializing in spycraft and Grant in history, mythology and astronomy.
*'''Expert Tactician''': Spector is a great strategist, being able to formulate different plans to assassinate his targets, infiltrate different locations, and escape from his enemies during his time as a spy and a mercenary.
{{Quote|Egyptians invented modern navigation. There's not a lot of landmarks in the desert. So they came up with a way to get about using the sun and the stars.|Steven Grant to [[Layla El-Faouly]]|The Friendly Type}}
*'''Master Scientist''': [[File:Etoile.png|thumb|250px|Grant assembles fragments into a star map]] Due to his passion for ancient [[Egypt]], Grant is extremely knowledgeable in the fields of history, archaeology, astronomy and Egyptology. He knows much about ancient Egyptians' practices, rituals and way of life, which came in great help during the search for the tomb of [[Ammit]]. Due to his knowledge, Grant could not contain his excitement when he figured out that his pursuit of the Disciples of Ammit had led him to the lost [[Tomb of Alexander the Great|tomb]] of [[Alexander the Great]].
*'''Master Investigator''': Grant was able to find the location of [[Ammit]]'s ushabti only with a few clues and drawing a picture in the sand.
*'''Expert Thief''': Spector was able to successfully steal the [[Scarab of Ammit]] from Arthur Harrow.
{{Quote|So, you're learning French and hieroglyphics?"<br>"Yeah, well... that's not that impressive, really.|[[Layla El-Faouly]] and Steven Grant|Summon the Suit}}
*'''Multilingualism''': Spector, Grant, and Lockley are all fluent in their native English. In addition, Spector is fluent in Arabic, Lockley is fluent in Spanish, while Grant is fluent in French, as demonstrated when he recited Marceline Desbordes-Valmore's poem "Les séparés". Grant can also understand ancient Egyptian in order to read hieroglyphs, and had some familiarity with Mandarin Chinese as he recognized [[Jamila]] and [[Arthur Harrow|Harrow]] speaking the dialect. Grant also understood Macedonian writing when he entered the tomb of [[Alexander the Great]].

==Equipment==
===Uniforms===
*'''[[Moon Knight's Suit|Moon Knight Suit]]''': A ceremonial suit of armor granted by [[Khonshu]] to Marc Spector. He wears the suit whenever fighting crime as Moon Knight. The suit can appear differently depending on which alter is in control. It gives Marc the use of the [[Crescent Darts]].
*'''[[Mr. Knight's Suit|Mr. Knight Suit]]''': Steven Grant's ceremonial suit of armor granted by [[Khonshu]]. Worn by Grant while operating as Mr. Knight. It gives Steven the ability to summon [[Mr. Knight's Truncheons]].

===Weapons===
*'''[[Crescent Darts]]''': Spector wielded the Crescent Darts as he fought a [[Jackals|jackal]], pulling one out of the emblem on his suit, which acts as both an emblem and a weapon. He later threw them with great skill at [[Anton Mogart]] and his thugs.
*'''[[Mr. Knight's Truncheons|Truncheons]]''': Mr. Knight's primary weapons are two metal staves, and can be summoned from nothing. Moon Knight also wielded them who used a hidden grappling device in them during his final fight with Arthur Harrow.
*'''{{WPS|Glock|Glock 17}}''': As a mercenary, Spector carried a pistol as his sidearm. After he was injured by Bushman, he attempted to commit suicide, but was saved by [[Khonshu]].
{{Quote|Did he just throw the gun?|[[Khonshu]]|The Goldfish Problem}}
*'''{{WPS|Glock|Glock 19}}''': Spector wielded a pistol in the Alps, but was quickly discarded when a confused Grant took over.
*'''{{WPS|Beretta 92FS Inox}}''': Grant found another pistol in Spector's gym bag.
*'''{{WPS|Colt Government Model}}''': Spector swiftly disarmed [[Bek]] of his pistol, but was encouraged by Layla to return it as they were temporarily outnumbered.
*'''{{WPS|AK-47}}''': Spector disarmed one of Harrow's followers of his rifle.
*'''[[Alexander the Great]]'s Axe''': Spector grabbed Alexander the Great's axe in the latter's coffin to hold Harrow and his men back in order to buy Layla some time to escape. He later lost the axe when he threw it at one of Harrow's men.
*'''Baseball Bat''': Grant grabbed this bat that was dropped by a sand zombie from the deck when he decided to protect Spector from being tossed overboard. He later discarded the bat when he saved Spector from being pulled into the dune sea, albeit at the cost of his own life.
*'''{{WPS|Beretta|Beretta Pistol}}''': Lockley utilized the pistol in order to kill [[Arthur Harrow]] and [[Ammit]].

===Vehicles===
*'''{{WPS|Rolls-Royce Phantom VIII|Rolls-Royce Phantom VIII Limousine}}''': Lockley drives around in a limousine that has a license plate that reads "SPKTR."

==Facilities==
*'''[[Steven Grant's Apartment]]''': The apartment in [[London]] is occupied by Grant and his goldfish, [[Gus (Fish)|Gus]]. It is a large apartment within a multi floored complex, equipped with ankle restraints to combat Grant's sleeping disorder. Spector also hid a key to his storage hideout and a cellphone to contact [[Layla El-Faouly]] at the apartment.
*'''[[National Art Gallery]]''': Grant used to work at the National Art Gallery as a gift shop employee, after being denied of a position as a tour guide. However, when [[Arthur Harrow]] sent a [[Jackals|jackal]] to attack Grant, it was killed by Moon Knight, during which a museum bathroom was damaged. Grant was let go from his job at the museum after he is blamed for the damages, in exchange for not pressing any charges against him.
*'''[[Khonshu's Temple]]''': Marc met Khonshu in his temple after he was shot by his former ally [[Raul Bushman]], where he was offered a second chance at life, in exchange for his servitude to Khonshu as his Fist of Vengeance.

