==Trivia==
*In the comics, Moon Knight joined many groups, including the [[Defenders]] and the West Coast [[Avengers]], but always left due to his inability to play well with others.
*One of the comic Moon Knight's alters in [[w:c:Marvel:Moon Knight Vol 8|Moon Knight Vol 8]] is a movie producer named Steven Grant, who perceives Moon Knight's actions as scenes in an MCU movie about Moon Knight that Grant is producing.
*Moon Knight shares the same birthday as [[Oscar Isaac]].
*Moon Knight was referenced in ''[[Doctor Strange (film)|Doctor Strange]]'', where one of the relics in the [[New York Sanctum]] is a white mask with an ankh next to it.
*Moon Knight is the second character in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] to be diagnosed with {{WPS|dissociative identity disorder}} after [[Mary Walker]].
*The alter of Steven Grant is known as a fictive, an alter that was based on a fictional character.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Ross Marquand]] previously expressed interest in playing Moon Knight.<ref>[https://comicbook.com/marvel/news/avengers-infinity-war-ross-marquand-red-skull-return-play-moon-knight-marvel/ ‘Avengers: Infinity War's Ross Marquand on Red Skull Return and Playing Marvel's Moon Knight]</ref>
*For scenes in which Marc Spector and Steven Grant interact with each other, [[Oscar Isaac]]'s brother [[Michael Benjamin Hernandez]] would stand in for one alter while Isaac portrayed the other.
*[[Jamel Blissat]], [[Attila Kosztor]], [[Daren Nop]] and [[Adrien Bour]] were stunt doubles for [[Oscar Isaac]] in the role of Moon Knight.

